Elder statesman Ben Nwabueze and PDP’s presidential candidate Atiku Abubakar had an emotional moment that kept social media buzzing Wednesday.
The 86-year-old SAN, activist, and leader of the thoughts in the southeast said he would resist death until he sees Atiku become president.
he spokesman of the Atiku Abubakar presidential campaign organisation, Segun Showunmi shared a picture of both men in a warm embrace.
Atiku himself would later share the pictures on his Twitter account, describing Nwabueze as a patriot and leading constitutional lawyer in Nigeria.
“In a very emotional meeting in Enugu, he reminded me of the unfinished Nigerian Project. I assure him, and every Nigerian, that I’ll keep my word,” he tweeted.
